episodes.title: Finale pt 1 (aka Halftime)
episodes.description:
This is part 1 of our final episode (or Halftime if you're Reid Priddy).

LOTS OF LAUGHS in this episode.

We gathered as many of the people involved in helping create 10+ years of The Net Live on one episode.  The show starts off with Kevin, DJ Roueche, Reid Priddy and Chris "Geeter" McGee.  The four of them go through the timeline of the show and MANY laughs were had.

Dan Maddon, Dustin Avol, Reid Lambourne and Katie Charles all make a guest apperance.

episodes.title: Misty May-Treanor The First Will Be Last Edition
episodes.description:
The Net Live crew brings everything full circle for our last episode.  

Misty May-Treanor was the very first guest back in 2009 and now our last guest.  

In this episode, Misty is on a VERY important mission while discussing her life post playing career.  She talks about her decision to coach at Long Beach City College, her dance moves on the AVP Tour and what life is like for her and her family now.


We couldn't be more grateful Misty took the time out of her busy life to call in and make out last episode even more special.

episodes.title: The Net Live  12/16/19 - Christmas Unspectacular Edition
episodes.description: Women's Final Four is all set for Pittsburgh / Men's Season is coming up.  Plus we haven't had Rich in studio forever.    Jay makes his annual journey West to join TNL for a day.  Tune in.

episodes.title: Take The Gold Edition with Maddison McKibbin
episodes.description:
We're not done yet.  Barnett and DJ Roueche are joined by one half of The McKibbon Brothers aka the bearded bros, Maddison McKibbon.  Maddison was kind enough to sit in the entire episode as we discussed the AVP Player Awards Banquet, the Olympic race, his YouTube channel and even a little Snow Volleyball.



Rich Lambourne called in at the beginning of the show to help recap the AVP Awards Banquet.  Some thing we could talk about, others, not so much.  He also helped break down the points race heading in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.


Check out The McKibbin Brothers YouTube channel.  You won't be dissapoointed.


Also, The Net Live can be heard on iTunes and Spotify.

TheNetLiveShow.com

episodes.title: It's About Team Edition
episodes.description:
Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche recap AVP Chicago, FIVB Rome Finals & chat with USA Men's Indoor and UCLA Men's Indoor Head Coach, John Speraw.  

Coach Speraw talks First Point Volleyball Foundation and upcoming World Cup.

http://firstpointvolleyball.com/

episodes.title: TNL co-founder to MBO Champion Edition
episodes.description:
AVP Manhattan Beach Open Champion, Reid Priddy, calls in to discuss his movie ready championship run with Trevor Crabb, his plans for the next couple AVP Events and his continued journey towards Tokyo.


Barnett and DJ Roueche discuss everything else about the MBO weekend, recap AVP Hermosa Beach, the US Men's Olympic Team qualifying for Tokyo and the remaining AVP events in Chicago and Hawaii.

episodes.title: Volleyball, Volleyball and More Volleyball Edition
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche, after about 12 minutes start talking about everything in the world of Volleyball.  VNL Finals (Men & Women), FIVB Beach World Champs and Gstaad, Current Olympic Standings with preview of what's to come now that we are in the meat of qualifications for Tokyo 2020.

Barnett and DJ Roueche are back after a few weeks off.  The passing of Eric Zaun is discussed.

We also recap VNL, AVP Austin & New York and FIVB Warsaw.

episodes.description: After a BIG weekend for the Sport of Volleyball, Kevin Barnett, DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne talk all things Volleyball (and a brief mention of it being Lambourne's birthday).  The guys recap AVP Huntington Beach, NCAA Beach Championship in Gulf Shores and Men's Indoor Championship from Long Beach.

episodes.description:
Kelly Reed - Producer extrordinairre for FIVB / AVP as well as other monsterous sporting events sits in with guest host Mark Schuerman.  

Plus CVW talks about the now complete 7-Team Men's field.   

Aother volley-rich edition of TNL

episodes.description: Casey Patterson brings the BOOM in studio to talk about how he got started playing volleyball, his partnerships throughout the years and this upcoming season.  College Volleyball Weekly discusses the BIG matches from this past weekend.

episodes.description: Big matches completed / Bigger matches coming up.   The men's season is streaking to a close.  Be in the know headed to the final week of regular season VB.

episodes.title: Can you spell You-Rang-Go Edition
episodes.description: AVP Pro, Geena Urango, join Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche live in studio.  Geena talks about her partnerships, goals for 2019 and her recent travels to Patagonia.  We also hear from our College Volleyball Weekly correspondents and discuss cats falling from Barnett's ceiling.

episodes.title: Respectful Heckle Edition
episodes.description:
DJ Roueche and Mark Scheurmann chat with recently retired AVP Pro and current Loyola Maramount Beach Head Coach, John Mayer.  John discusses his full time coaching career and how mad he was at DJ Roueche during the 2015 AVP Awards banquet.

The College Volleyball Weekly crew discuss the new #1 men's team in the country as we get close to tournament time.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 3/18/19 - Off Script Edition
episodes.description: Richy USA makes a long awaited return to the TNL Studio.  Beach report from Rich / CVW / LeBron James / College Admissions Issues / Does DJ Roueche play music from embattled artists?  All that and more on this episode of your favorite VB Show.

episodes.title: Jeff Nygard, USC Head Coach Edition
episodes.description:
Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche, back together after a couple weeks away from each other, chat with USC Men's Head Coach, Jeff Nygard, College Volleyball Weekly and Refereering at BYU.

And there is some other entertaining nonsense discussed, as always

episodes.title: Next Level Pull-Ability with Sarah Pavan Edition
episodes.description: AVP Announcer Mark Schuermann sits in for Kevin Barnett.  Mark and DJ Roueche chat with Canadian Beach player Sarah Pavan live in studio.  Sarah gives some great background on her journey to become a top beach player.  The CVW boys call in to update the men's college game and everything else in the sport of volleyball.

episodes.title: We Were Kings Edition
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett & DJ Roueche have the first ever TNL Book Club with Author, Sports Writer and Volleyball player, Travis Mewhirter, to discuss his book "We Were Kings", which is available on Amazon.  BYU Men's Head Coach Shawn Olmstead talks his current team before their match against UCLA, College Volleyball Weekly upate and we discuss the two lawsuits that have been filed against p1440 & Dave Mays.

episodes.title: "I know they got swept, but they had them on the ropes" - Edition
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche are joined in studio by Princeton University Head Coach. We chat missed calls by referees, College Volleyball and everything else in the volleyball world.

episodes.title: Kevin Hambly talks Stanford National Championship
episodes.description: The first episode of year 10 for The Net Live kicks off with Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche chatting with Kevin Hambly about coaching Stanford Women to a National Championship, youth club volleyball, TNL book club, reflecting on the Casey Jennings interveiw, AVP 2019 schedule and College Volleyball Weekly.

episodes.title: Casey Jennings Edition - The Net Live
episodes.description: Casey Jennings and the TNL crew have a spirited conversation about p1440.  We also got our College Volleyball Weekly correspondent talking NCAA Women's VB Semifinals/Finals happening this week in Minneapolis.

episodes.title: The Lion King (Aleksandrs Samoilovs) Edition
episodes.description: We are honored to be joined by The Lion King, live in studio, Aleksandrs Samoilovs talks his volleyball career and where the Lion King nickname came from.  We're also joined by Gilad Jacobs, founder of Normatec, who discusses the importance of recovery in todays sports world.  And our college volleyball weekly correspondence talk the final 16 teams in Women's College Volleyball.

episodes.title: No More Phake Phil Edition - The Net Live
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche get the show going right away with College Volleyball Weekly as the field of 64 is set.  Blair Lambert gives us an international update followed by a AVP Men's player partner changes, p1440 preview and Kevin wanting "no more fake Phil".

episodes.title: Karch Kiraly talks National Team Season
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett, DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne are joined by Women's National Team Coach, Karch Kiraly as he recaps the National Team seaon.  Brandon Rosenthal with College Volleyball Weekly and Blair Lambert gives us an update on the USA Players on their international teams.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 11/7/18 - Kevin and DJ Roueche Disagree Edition
episodes.description:
Barnett and DJ Roueche disagree on coaching styles but also discuss everything else is the world of Volleyball.

Plus CVW is heading toward the playoffs and things get interesting with Kyle and Brandon.

episodes.title: The Net Live - I've Never Lost a Rap Battle Edition feat. Dave Mays of p1440
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche recap the USA Women's 5th place finish in World Championship and are joined by a p1440 founder, Dave Mays.

episodes.title: John Speraw chats World Championships Bronze Medal
episodes.description: Barnett, Rich Lambourne & DJ Roueche chat with John Speraw about the men's teams Bronze Medal in World Championships.  We recap the weeks in Women's College Volleyball and of course chat about everything else in the world of Volleyball.

episodes.title: FIVB Indoor World Championships & p1440 recap - The Net Live
episodes.description: After a morning workout on the beach, Barnett, Lambourne and DJ Roueche discuss p1440 San Jose, Indoor World Championships and a chat with Brandon Rosenthal & Kyle Walton for College Volleyball weekly.

episodes.title: King of the Court recap edition - The Net Live
episodes.description:
After 4 weeks on the road DJ Roueche is back along with Kevin Barnett to recap the King of the Court series, AVP Chicago and Hawaii with preview of p1440 San Jose.  We also chat with Jake Roehl of Fit Bar.

www.fit-bar.com

episodes.title: The Net Live - What are "real" points Edition
episodes.description: Barnett is back from his Euro vacation and along with DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne discuss p1440, AVP Chicago, have a conversation about "real" points on the beach and 2018's first Fall Edition of College Volleyball Weekly.

episodes.title: The Net Live - Manhattan Beach Recap & King of The Court preview with Team JRich
episodes.description: Rich Lambourne joins DJ Roueche as they recap another amazing AVP Manhattan Beach Open and they preview the new King of the Court series.

episodes.title: The Net Live - Nicolette Martin Edition 08/06/18
episodes.description:
Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche are joined by Nicolette Martin who talks about her skills off the beach.  Check out her artwork at NicoletteArt.com

We also discuss potential partnership changes on the beach, Seaside/AVP Next event, airline travel and 6man.

episodes.title: The Net Live - Carly Wopat, Five 12 Apparel & AVP Recap Edition
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett & DJ Roueche recap AVP Hermosa, are joined in studio by Nationa Team member Carly Wopat and they visit with Ali Wood of Five 12 Apparel.

episodes.title: The Net Live - Kelsey Robinson + AVP San Fran Edition
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche are back from AVP San Fran chatting about that event, VNL recap and are joined in the studio by Women's National Team Member, Kelsey Robinson.

episodes.title: The Net Live - AVP Seattle and VNL recap
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche are back from AVP Seattle, recapping a great tournament at Lake Sammamish and discussing our indoor national teams who will be playing in the VNL Final rounds this weekend

episodes.title: The Net Live - DJ Roueche Birthday Week Edition
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche recap VNL, AVP New York along with upcoming VNL matches for the men in Italy and the women in China and AVP Seattle.  James Wilroy, Genius Sports, calls in to discuss statistics for the future of Volleyball.

episodes.title: 6/4/18 The Net Live - Sitting Gold In Dallas Edition
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche return with their GOLD MEDALS after winning the Sitting Division at USAV Adult Nationals.  They recap their Dallas experience, team USA's VNL matches and a preview of AVP New York.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 5/21/18 The Amazon Prime AVP Austin Edition
episodes.description: Kevin Barnett (aka The New Beach Guy) and DJ Roueche are back from Austin, TX with a special recap edition of how things went at the first AVP Tournament of the season and the Ground Breaking coverage of the AVP on Amazon Prime.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 5/7/18 Volleyball Hangover Edition
episodes.description: It was busy weekend in the world of volleyball.  Barnett and DJ Roueche discuss the AVP/FIVB Huntington Beach event, NCAA Women's Beach Volleyball National Championship, NCAA Men's Indoor National Championship and are joined by Mike Griffin from Bad Boys Volleyball Open & Seaside Volleyball Tournament along with the final CVW Men's edition wrapping up the college men's season.

episodes.title: The Net Live 4/30/18 - BIGGEST VB Week of the Year Edition
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche discuss the BIG upcoming week in the world of Volleyball (FIVB/AVP, Men's College VB Championship, Womens's Beach VB Championship) and are joined live in studio by Tim Kelly from Bring It On Promotions.

episodes.title: TNL 4/16/18 - Attitude Adjustment Edition
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche talk about USA doing well in NORCECA, Frienimies, Attitude Adjustment (including their own adjustments) and College Volleyball playoffs.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 4/9/18 Team TNL reunited
episodes.description: Team TNL reunited as Kevin Barnett and DJ Roueche discuss College Beach Volleyball, Men's College Indoor volleyball and everything else that comes up during the normal course of the podcast.

episodes.title: The Net Live 3/26/18 Beach Partner Carousel
episodes.description: Mark Schuermann sits in for Kevin Barnett and along with DJ Roueche and Rick Lambourne, they discuss new partnerships on the Women's Beach side, upcoming FIVB/AVP event in Huntington Beach and everything else in the sport of Volleyball.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 03/19/18 - Canadian Bacon Edition
episodes.description:
Sam Pedlow has been rising along with Canadian Volleyball in general, both indoors and out.  Hear his story as he drops in live.

Also, CVW takes on some upsets and the looming playoffs in Men's Indoor.

That and more of the usual nonsense on TNL.

episodes.title: The inmates have taken over Edition - The Net Live 3/12/18
episodes.description: Barnett is away so DJ Roueche is joined by Rich Lambourne, Natalie Hagglund and George Mason head coach, Jay Hosack live in studio to discuss everything in the world of volleyball.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 03/05/18 - Beach is Underway Edition
episodes.description:
Kevin and Jeremy are holding the Home Court.  Beach is underway so you know JRo will be pumped.

Plus College Men's put up some action last week.  Hear about the changes and challenges coming out of the middle of the season.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 02/26/18 - We tricked Natalie Edition
episodes.description:
The Olympics are a wrap, Did Natalie do her homework?  Does she know "Toe Pick"? 

Recruiting timelines is a hot topic these days.  Hear from someone who recently went through the process and school.

CVW:  Features upsets galore.  Conf. and Non Conf. action has been exciting this last week, with two matches between #1 LBSU and #2 UCLA.  Do they hold thier positions in the polls?  Who's the favorite after this week's action?

episodes.title: The Net Live - 02/12/18 - Welcome Natalie Hagglund Edition
episodes.description:
Natalie Hagglund was an amazing college libero.  She trained with Team USA right until the 2016 Rio Olympic Games.  She will be joining the TNL crew a number of times in the next few weeks.  This is show 1. 

Also, Kerri Walsh Jennings and the world of BVB athletes have created a Players Union.  What is the reason for it's creation / What will be the effect and where do things go from here?  Answers for you.

Plus whatever else we think of during a normal Monday morning.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 02/5/18 - First Ever Celebration Edition
episodes.description:
In studio, Kevin Jro and Rich talk about all things volleyball this last week in addition to relating Super Bowls to Olympic Games.

All new TNL Today.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 01/29/18 - Pre SuperBowl Edition
episodes.description:
Hear from the National Championship winning head coach one month later.  He's back into the grind of "the next", but we will reflect on another outstanding Christmas celebration for the Huskers.

The Head man at Princeton, Sam Schweisky, sits in with us once again to talk all things "Program Building" and why it's an exciting time for the Tigers program.

Plus Rich and Reid bring in some sand to the studio.  Fresh off practice and getting ready for another BVB season.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 1/22/18 - Trash Talk on the Beach Edition
episodes.description: Mark Schuermann sitting in for Barnett joins DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne to discuss trash talking on the beach, CVW an Mark's interview with Wade Garard with MotorMVB.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 01/08/18 - Welcome to Year 9 Edition
episodes.description:
Off we go into Year 9 covering the VB world.  New technology has emerged in the 9 years we've been on air.  Today we talk with Hector Negron of The SpikeNet - A streaming platform providing increased exposure to all things volleyball at several levels and special events.  Hear where spectators of the game are headed in 2018 and beyond.

Plus CVW for the Men's Season gets started.  The drive to UCLA in May and a possible National Title starts now.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 12/18/17  -  Nicole Davis Edition
episodes.description:
Nicole Davis is a two-time Silver medalist and now works for Dr. Michael Gevais.  We'll visit with her about all things volleyball and post career.

Plus the crew is back from Kansas City and ready to put a bow on the Championships.  

Tune in!

episodes.title: TNL Takes on Kansas City AVCA Convention Pt. 2
episodes.description: The TNL Crew decends upon Kansas City for their annual AVCA Convention show from the Volley Metrics booth.  Part two of our conversatins with Coaches, Players, friends of the show and much more stop by for a chat.

episodes.title: TNL Takes on Kansas City Convention Pt. 1
episodes.description: The TNL Crew decends upon Kansas City for their annual AVCA Convention show from the Volley Metrics booth.  Coaches, Players, friends of the show and much more stop by for a chat.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 12/12/17 - Final Four Coaches + Holiday Spectacular Edition
episodes.description:
Penn State v. Nebraska and Stanford v. Florida are happening on Thursday night.  Hear from all four coaches involved.  Russ Rose, John Cook, Kevin Hambly and Mary WIse all join the TNL Crew.  

Plus the Annual Holiday Spectacular holds down the patio level.  Kevin, Jeremy, Rich, Jay, Robbie and more all on TNL.

Tune IN!!!!

episodes.title: The Net Live - 12/4/17  -  Christmas Gift Giving Edition - Kelly Reeves
episodes.description:
We get you ready for the holidays with our gift guide advice.  TNL Merch / USAV Gear from Adidas / Rollers and more from Hyperice

Also, we give you another in studio performance.  Kelly Reeves of UCLA and now a rising star on the AVP Tour stops in to talk about life as a young baller.  Plus Christine Shelby of Adidas calls in from Germany to discuss the launch of the line and signing of new athletes to the #3StripeLife.

Also, we talk field of 16 and the move to the Final Four next week in KC.  Exciting times in Volleyball.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 11/27/17  -  Cyber Monday Blowout Sale Edition
episodes.description:
NCAA Field of 64 was announced yesterday - Who's in Who's out and what does it all look like for the journey to KC?  The CVW guys will give you thier takes on the upcoming tourney.

Matt Prosser was winning tournaments and on his was to VB lore when the music stopped in 2010.  Hear from him on what was and what is for a top level pro of that era.

Plus, Erik Shoji calls in from Italy to talk about his new business endevour.  You do not want to miss an opportunity to get involved with him.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 11/13/17  -  Karsta Lowe Edition
episodes.description:
Karsta Lowe had an incredible rise through the volleyball world culminating with a bronze medal in Rio.  She stops by to talk volley life and real life as she has embarked on a new adventure outside of sports.

CVW talks upsets and rankings as the final two weeks of regular season women's volleyball are underway.  The final fornight journey to a potential playoff opportunity.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 11/6/17 - Brittany Hochevar in Studio
episodes.description:
Getting your name on the Pier is special.  Getting it on there twice is priceless.  Brittany Hochevar joins us in studio to talk about the greatest stretch of volleyball in career over the past 18 months.  Longevity secrets shall be yours.

Plus, AVP post season awards, News on Nat. Team athletes overseas and CVW continues the run toward the post season.  The Selection Committee gave us their first rankings this week.  FInd out where your favorite teams landed and how the field of 64 is shaping up.

All that plus the usual delightful mess that is TNL.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 10/30/17  -  Return of Jeremy Edition
episodes.description: Welcome back Jeremy Roueche.  JRo took his longest break in the history of his TNL involvement.  Hear what he's been up to and what's ahead.  We'll also talk volleyball at some point.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 10/30/17  -  Return of Jeremy Edition

episodes.description:
The USA Men's National Team season is officially over.  We'll put a bow on it for you.   

Politics in Sports?  Olympics sports?

CVW returns to look at the continued weird world of women's college competition.

Plus Richy USA is back in studio

episodes.title: The Net Live - 9/18/17 - Another Short Offering
episodes.description: Another TNL Episode for your pleasure.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 9/11/17 - Special Edition
episodes.description: Kevin and the TNL Crew cover some college ground on this special quick hit of TNL.

episodes.title: USA Cup Interviews 4 of 4 - Lauren Carlini
episodes.description: Lauren Carlini had a stellar career at Wisconsin and arrives at Team USA with a ton of promise.  Her Senior National Team Career got underway in USA Cup Match 2 in Anaheim last night.  Her #1 fan was definitely watching.  The question is, does he need a new phone today?

episodes.title: USA Cup Interviews 3 of 4 - Foluke Akinradewo
episodes.description: Olympian Foluke Akinradewo has been a huge part of Team USA's middle attack.  She's back on court with some off court changes.  Hear all about it from Anaheim post USA Cup match #2.

episodes.title: USA Cup Interviews 2 of 4 - CEO Jamie Davis and Opposite Hitter Annie Drews
episodes.description: Jamie Davis has been on the job since January, hear his thoughts on joining the VB world from the outside.   Plus Annie Drews has made a big splash on the National Team.  Has Team USA found it's opposite?  Hear from the new kid on the starting six.

episodes.title: USA Cup Interviews 1 of 4 - Carli Lloyd and Madi Kingdon
episodes.description: Veteran and starting setter Carli Lloyd shares her thoughts on the year thus far with Team USA.  Also, Madi Kingdon has broken into the rotation at OH this year.  Hear her reflect on 2017 and thoughts on going to South Korea for the professional season

episodes.title: The Net Live - 8/28/17 - Sprint to the Finish Edition w/Karch + Adidas
episodes.description:
The TNL Crew welcomes in Karch Kiraly to wrap up Grand Prix / talk USA Cup v. Brazil and the prospects for a Grand Champions Cup Title.

Also, Christine Shelby of Adidas USA joins us to discuss her company's push into volleyball.  They own the National Teams, now hear the strategic plan for all out volley domination.

The crew also looks forward to AVP Chicago after a Phil and Nick win in Germany this past weekend.

All that plus College Volleyball Weekly is back in full force with upsets throughout the Top 10.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 8/21/17 - Total Eclipse of the Sun Edition
episodes.description:
Team JRich and Team Nicole are in studio, along with Reid Priddy and his camera crew to help wrap a weekend of VB at Manhattan Beach.  Also, Women's NCAA starts another season this week, the CVW crew checks in for the first time this Fall.

The Indoor National Teams are also under new sponsorship with Adidas and we find out how it all went down.  Christine Shelby of Adidas USA joins us.

That and so much more on TN

episodes.title: The Net Live - 8/7/17 - Is Summer Over Yet Edition
episodes.description:
What happened in China?  What happened in Vienna?  Hear from those that covered and participated in the events.  Rich is back from VIenna and Kevin is back from the upside down where he covered the GP.

Plus Women's College Volleyball is just underway.  Practices have begun and classes start next.  We talk to Kelly Miller of Ball State about the Cardinals chances this season.  Chirp Chirp, it's another week of TNL.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 7/31/17 - Goodbye July Edition
episodes.description: Kevin and JRo hold down the home court for another episode.

episodes.title: Special World Champs Interview - RichyUSA with Emily Day and Nicole Branagh
episodes.description: Richy sits down with Emily and Nicole to get the 411 on how it all came to be and the tournament so far.  TNL from Vienna and the FIVB World Championships.  Enjoy

episodes.title: The Net Live - 7/24/17 - We are in Town Edition
episodes.description:
With World League over, we catch up with John Speraw and disect the Men's Tournament.  

The Women's Team is headed into Grand Prix Finals in one week.  We break down that tournament so far.

Plus the Beach is in full effect. WSOBVB, AVP Hermosa, FIVB Poland and upcoming the World Championships from Vienna.  

So much to cover and we'll give it to you in this episode.

TUNE IN!!!

episodes.title: TNL People - Marv Dunphy: Legendary Head Coach
episodes.description: A visit with the legendary 1988 Gold Medal winning coach and longtime head man at Pepperdine.  He's announced his retirement from the University, but it's not the last you've heard of Marv.

episodes.title: Part 2 - Team J-Rich, again
episodes.description:
Part 2 of the DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne, aka Team J-Rich, takeover and this time talk 90% beach volleyball sprinkled in with a little N'SYNC, Saturday Night Live and indoor volleyball talk.

Recap FIVB, AVP & WSOBV events from the last few weeks.

episodes.title: The Net Live 07/17/17 - Pt. 1 - Team J-Rich Edition, again.
episodes.description:
Part 1 of the DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne, aka Team J-Rich, takeover and this time talk 90% beach volleyball sprinkled in with a little N'SYNC, Saturday Night Live and indoor volleyball talk.

Recap FIVB, AVP & WSOBV events from the last few weeks.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 6/19/17 - Another Show Edition
episodes.description:
World League Week 3 and a look forward to the World League Finals

FIVB The Hague review and more from Kevin, Jeremy and Rich

episodes.title: Full Summer Swing Edition
episodes.description: AVP New York  /  World League Week 2  /  FIVB Hague Preview  /  Week 3 World League Preview and whatever else comes up on TNL.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 6/5/17 USAV Adult Nationals Recap Edition and Curling
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche fresh off their trip to Minnesota for USAV Adult Nationals will be joined by USA Sitting Volleyball team member, J Dee Marinko, and Olympic Gold Medalist Lloy Ball.  World League and Team Sit Happens recaps.

episodes.title: TNL Special Feature:  National Team Practice Interviews 5/22/17
episodes.description: Feel as though you are in Southern California just hanging out in the gym as the National Teams prepare for Year 1 of the Olympic journey.  Barnett catches up with Dustin Watten / James Shaw / Andrea Becker and Karch Kiraly and you are in the conversation.

episodes.title: The Net Live Show #332 - 5/15/17 - USC and World League Ramp Up Edition
episodes.description: Players turning pro / Players telling the FIVB they are wrong / World League looming / National Teams coming back together / Team Kevin v. Team Jeremy,  and more on a TNL Monday.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 5/8/17 - Championship Edition
episodes.description:
NCAA Men's Indoor from Ohio State, NCAA BVB from Gulf Shores, AVP from Huntington Beach, News on the future of Kerri Walsh Jennings and more all in a crazy weekend of VB.

The TNL crew packs in a full house with Kevin, Jeremy, Rich and Nicole to talk about the week that was.  Broadcaster, DJ, Coach and Player - We have every perspective on the weekend covered for you.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 5/1/17 - All VB Edition
episodes.description:
The Super Six is happening this week along with the NCAA Beach VB Championships and the AVP Huntington Beach.  If you are a fan of volleyball, this is your opening weekend.

2017 gets going NOW!

episodes.title: The Net Live - 04/24/17 It's Deja Vu All Over Again
episodes.description: Stop us if you've heard this before.....Barnett and DJ Roueche discuss the WSOBV, NVL and AVP joining and CVW discuss the "Super Six".  We're also joined by Megan Kaplon & Katie Kabbes, the ladies behind Flo Volleyball.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 4/17/17 - JRo Nuptials Edition
episodes.description:
The biggest player in the game is suing the domestic tour.  What will be the effects on the sport at large and this upcoming summer of play?  Rich, Kevin and Jeremy unpack it for you.

The Men's Conference playoffs are underway.  Who's still in, who's done till 18' and what's happening this week?  Questions answered by Vinnie, Jay and Robbie

That and a full recap of the JRo Wedding and Suicide Doors performance (plus a critique of Barnett's dance moves) up on this episode of TNL

episodes.title: The Net Live 4/3/17 - Historical Edition of TNL
episodes.description:
A week of crazy in college VB.   BVB Players continue to get ready for the season and new partnerships are getting put together.  Where will players play this summer, How will they choose tournaments?

College Men's is almost over.  EIVA, MIVA, MPSF and Conference Carolinas are all into their last week of regular season.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 3/27/17 - Mark Rules the World Edition
episodes.description: Kevin is out for the day which means DJ Roueche gets a chance to further Team JRo.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 3/20/17 - Live Feed #1
episodes.description:
DJ Roueche and Kevin hold down the home court as they have done for the past 5 years.  


	Dustin Watten of the Men's Indoor National Team calls in, from Poland, to talk Nutrition / National Team and Travel.  


	Plus the AVCA College Volleyball Weekly and more nonsense on TNL.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 3/13/17 - Spring Forward Edition
episodes.description:
Jay Hosak joins the crew in studio.  


	Kathy DeBoer of the AVCA calls into the program to talk about college beach.


	That and Reid Priddy stops by.

episodes.title: The Net Live 03/06/17 - Mark + JRo Edition
episodes.description: Mark Schuermann and DJ Roueche are in charge of the program with Lambourne.  The guys are joined by John Speraw who discusses UCLA and the National Team, Brandon Rosenthal gives a recap on the USA Volleyball Open Tryouts from Colorado Springs and of course College Volleyball Weekly.

episodes.title: The Net Live - Kevin gets a gift from Texas edition
episodes.description: Barnett is back in the Home Court with DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne.  We will be joined by new Netherlands Women's indoor Head Coach, Jamie Morrison.

episodes.title: TNL People - powered by the AVCA - Reid Priddy now playing Beach Volleyball
episodes.description: 4-Time Olympian, 2-Time Olympic Medalist (Gold and Bronze) and one of the founders of The Net Live, Reid Priddy joins DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne to discuss the transition and his mindset going into his first full season playing professional BEACH volleyball.

episodes.title: The Net Live - The All Beach, plus Kevin Hambly, Special Edition of TNL
episodes.description:
With Barnett our of town, DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne have highjacked the show to discuss only things going on in the world of Beach Volleyball, with a break to chat with the new Stanford women's indoor Head Coach Kevin Hambly.  Reid Priddy live in studio discussing his mindset now that he's training to compete on the beach full time.

It's the All Beach Special Edition of The Net Live.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 2/13/17 = #TeamKevin v Rich
episodes.description: Nicole and Kevin are ready for Rich and his humorless humor.   Tune in to get the full story on the Swatch Major Series kickoff.  Plus CVW and the normal stuff you expect from TNL.

episodes.title: The Net Live  01/30/17 - We kicked Kevin off Edition
episodes.description: Mark Schuermann takes over hosting duties from Barnett, along with DJ Roueche as they are joined by Princeton Men's Volleyball Head Coach, Sam Shweisky, Ohio State Men's Head Coach Pete Hanson and Scott Davenport & Adam Schulz from the newly formed AVP Academy.

episodes.title: The Net Live 1/23/17 - Someone Build an Ark Edition
episodes.description: Gold Medalist Scott Touzinsky, just retired from professional volleyball,  joins the crew to talk about the past and the future for he and his family.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 01/17/17 - How to Retire Edition
episodes.description:
John Dunning won 5 National Titles at 2 different schools.   He's decided to go out on top.   Hear him talk about coaching All Americans / recruiting to Stanford  and his plans for life after the game.

The CVW crew is in week 2 and what a crazy bunch of matches it was last week with the Men.  Is the midwest still the power in the game?    Can the West Coast get back in the title hunt?  Early projections and prognostications from Vinnie, Jay and Robbie.

Plus Nicole is back on Team Kevin.

episodes.title: The Net Live  - 01/09/17 The 2016 Nettie Awards Show
episodes.description:
The TNL Crew, Kevin / Jeremy and Rich hand out their yearly awards for 2016.  Best Moment / Most Influential Event Players of the Year and more.  The Netties are the annual cashless prizes given out by the show.

Plus, hear reaction to the new CEO of USAV / An update on the professional situation for the Men's players around the world / College Volleyball Weekly for the Men starts episode #1.

That and a whole lot more on episode 1 of Year 9

episodes.title: 12/26/16 - AVCA Columbus, OH Convention Special Pt. 2
episodes.description: The conclusion of DJ Roueche & Rich Lambourne's trip to the Polar Vortex as they chat with Oregon State Assistant Coach and Olympic Gold Medalist, Ron Zwerver, Rick Dunetz from the Side-Out Foundation, Sean Maniz of Belmont Abbey, Rob Neilson from Volleymetrics, our friends from TeamSnap and Anthony Katz of Hyperice.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 12/16/16 - AVCA Columbus, OH Convention Special Part 1
episodes.description: Part 1 of DJ Roueche and Rich Lambourne's attempt at hosting their first podcast without Kevin Barnett in Columbus, OH at the AVCA Convention.  Roueche and Lambourne chatted with Stanford Beach Head Coach, Andrew Fuller, Lee Feinswog of VolleyballMag.com, Lewis University Men's Head Coach, Dan Friend and AVP Announcer Mark Schuermann and Brandon Rosenthal, Head Coach at Lipscomb University.

episodes.title: The Net Live 12/12/16 - The Annual Holiday Spectacular
episodes.description:
The Annual Holiday Spectacular is on!   There will be food and drink / Laughter and Fun as we pack the house with all of our TNL hosts from the year plus other terrific volleyball people.   Plus, hear from all Four of the coaches headed to Columbus with thier teams to vie for a National Title.

Hugh McCutcheon, Jerritt Elliott, John Dunning and John Cook will join us.

Tune in for the best, and maybe by 11am the worst, TNL has to offer.

episodes.title: TNL People - powered by the AVCA - Kirsten Booth of Creighton University
episodes.description: The Creighton Bluejays are in the Sweet 16 for the second year in a row.  They knocked off #5 Kansas on the Jayhawks home floor 20-18 in the 5th set.  Hear from the Head Coach about the season, the program and the future for the baddest Mid-Major in the land.

episodes.title: TNL People - powered by the AVCA - Ted Baker Co-Founder of QALO
episodes.description: Active people require special equipment.  QALO has been making the original Silicone Rings since 2012.  Co-Founder Ted Baker sits in the Home Court to talk business, life, love and passion.  Get your entrepreneurial fix for the week courtesy of TNL.  That and a special offer for you, the listener, from QALO

episodes.title: The Net Live 12/05/16 - My Sweet 2016 Edition with a Ring
episodes.description:
Once upon a time there were 300+ teams with dreams of a National Title.  Just 16 remain in the game.  Hear from Creighton Bluejay head coach Kirsten Booth on how her team from Omaha kept their National Title aspirations alive this last week.

Also, the TNL crew wears them and you should too.  If you are an active married male or female your wedding band can take a beating.  QALO saw a need and filled it with a product you'll love.  Hear from the founder and creator of the original wedding band for active athletes everywhere.

That and More on TNL

episodes.title: I Am So Full, Give me the Field of 64 to Eat Edition
episodes.description: Here we go for the playoffs.  CVW Crew picks it apart as the TNL crew recovers from the Holiday.

episodes.title: The Net Live 11/22/16 - Turkey and Stuffing Edition
episodes.description:
Why does a coach announce she's leaving a top program in the middle of the playoff chase?  Find out first hand from Anne Kordes of Louisville.

Also, a 5-Time Olympian joins us to talk about Volleyball immortality and life after the game.  Danielle Scott, International Volleyball Hall of Fame Class 2016, calls in from Louisiana.

That and so much of the ususal with Kevin, Jeremy, Rich and Nicole in studio.

episodes.title: The Net Live 11/8/16 - BOOOOOOOM!!!! Edition
episodes.description:
Join Casey Patterson, Nicole Branaugh, Rich, Jeremy and Kevin for another day of Volleyball talk.

Also, College Volleyball Weekly updates with Brandon and Kyle.  Along with new CVW contributor Lee Feinswog.

That and more on TNL

episodes.title: The Net Live 10/24/16 - Halloween Edition with Misty May-Treanor
episodes.description: Barnett, Roueche & Lambourne talk volley, and other topics of course, on today's Halloween edition.  International Volleyball Hall of Fame Inductee Misty May-Treanor will call in to discuss the HOF ceremony from this past weekend.

episodes.title: The Net Live 10/17/16 - Seattle Weather Edition
episodes.description:
Kevin, Rich, Jeremy and Nicole hang in the Home Court.

Head Coach Rich Feller of CAL who has defeated Colorado and Arizona on consecutive Sunday afternoons joins the crew to talk about his team and his program's biggest win this season.

CVW with Brandon and Kyle reviewing the week in Collegiate Women's play.

Plus, a lot of the usual nonsense both Volleyball and Non-Volleyball related.

episodes.title: 10/11/16 The Net Live - Fall in the Middle of October Edition
episodes.description: We are joined in studio by Nicole Branagh and Rich Lambourne. David Folch from Dirty Sixer Bikes will be calling in along with Kevin Pratte from San Diego City College.

episodes.title: TNL People Powered by the AVCA - 2009 Phil Dalhausser
episodes.description: A look back at the beginnings of TNL and where Big Phillip stood 7 years ago.  Spend some time in the way back machine with TNL.

episodes.title: The Net Live 10/4/16 - Who Knows Whatever Edition
episodes.description:
KB, JR and RL all sit in talk about stuff.

Plus CVW and more on TNL

episodes.title: The Net Live 09/27/16 Nashville and DJ Roueche Rio Recap Edition
episodes.description: DJ Roueche is back from all of his travels, or at least home for a few days before his next flight, to recap his Olympic and Paralympic experience.  Paralympic Gold Medalist Katie Holloway calls in, Barnett and Roueche just returned from their TNL trip to Nashville, so expect lots of country music talk.  Along with College Volleyball Weekly and everything else in the world of Volleyball.

episodes.title: The Net Live 9/12/16 - Week 2 of Reality Edition
episodes.description:
Reid Priddy is in house and ready to talk about the future away from the National Team.  It's been 17 years of his life.  What's next?  Find out.

CVW is back again and talking the crazy pre conference results from another week of College Women's VB.

That and more international news and discussion on TNL

episodes.title: The Net Live 9/6/16 - Post Olympic Vacation + Return To Reality Edition
episodes.description: Christa Dietzen of the United States Women's Team sits in with Rich Lambourne and Kevin.  Also Camryn Irwin calls in from San Diego, fresh off her trip to Chicago.  We'll talk all things Olympics / Beach Post Games and celebrate Bronze on TNL's return to the airwaves.

episodes.title: The Net Live 7/25/16 - Pre Olympic BLOWOUT
episodes.description:
This is it.  DJ Roueche is about to become an Olympian.   Kevin is going for the fifth time and TNL will be shut down.  We are going to blow it out before catching a jet plane to Brazil.

Reviews of Grand Prix / World League and Beach Events

Reviews of Olympic Roster Selections

Previews of Olympic performances

That and more on TNL

episodes.title: The Net Live - John Speraw Special Lookback
episodes.description: On the eve of World League Finals take a listen to Head Coach John Speraw in 2013 and 2014.  Hear where he thought the team was during those seasons in preparation for this year's Olympic Games.    TNL History

episodes.title: The Net Live 07/02/16 On location from Dallas World League
episodes.description: LIVE from World League in Dallas during the Men's National Team practice, Barnett and DJ Roueche chat with Andrea Becker & Erik Sullivan from the MNT staff, Eddie Brown from Athlete Performance Solution and Two-Time Olympian Sean Rooney.

episodes.title: The Net Live 6/21/16 - Surf's Up Edition
episodes.description:
John Speraw has named the Olympic Team.  This is the earliest it has been named in some time.  Hear the crew's reaction to the 2016 Men's Olympic Team.

The CVW boys are in studio:  Jay Hosak and Rob Espero are present and accounted for.

We'll have recaps and analysis of Grand Prix Round 2 in Long Beach, WL Week 1 in Brazil, AVP New York City and FIVB Beach VB in Poland.

That and more on TNL

episodes.title: The Net Live 6/13/16 Gold Medalist Eric Fonoimoana
episodes.description: On today's show, FIVB Germany, World League getting underway, Grand Prix already underway and Olympic Gold Medalist Eric Fonoimoana joins us LIVE in studio.

episodes.title: The Net Live 6/6/16 - #SittingGoldInMN Edition
episodes.description: Volleyball is not the most important thing in the world - Samantha Rennie of Cal Men’s Olympic Field is Complete - We now know all the teams that will participate in Rio.  IN STUDIO - JRoAVP Seattle / FIVB Russia - Results and Updates on Olympic Qualification Situations.Bill Ferguson has a new jobTwo-Time Olympic Silver Medalist Heather Bown talks sitting

episodes.title: The Net Live 5/23/16 Pre #SittingGoldInOrlando Edition
episodes.description: The boys are back to discuss FIVB/AVP Cincy, Women's Indoor Field Estabilished for Rio, our upcoming trip for #SittingGoldOrlando and a new sponsor for The Net Live.

episodes.title: TNL People - Powered by the AVCA - USA Cup Night 2
episodes.description: Exclusive content from night #2 of USA Cup after the USA defeated Japan 3-0 in Long Beach. Gold Medalist Reid Priddy / Asst. Coach Matt Fuerbringer / Head Coach John Speraw, UCSB's Jonah Seif and All Star Setter Micah Christenson.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 5/9/16 - Spring Championship Blowout Edition
episodes.description: CVW - The Final Episode until late September.    Pete Hansen:  You knew one of the Super Six would be back this week.  And you know now it’s Ohio State’s Pete Hansen.   His second title in 6 seasons with the Buckeyes.  Brandon Rosenthal:  He was down in Gulf Shores, Alabama this weekend at the Inaugural Women’s Beach Volleyball National Championship.  Also, IN STUDIO - Jro and Katie CharlesAVP Huntington / FIVB in Sochi - Movement in the Olympic points / Champions crowned in Huntington Beach

episodes.title: The Net Live - 5/2/16 - the "Too Much Volley Info Edition"
episodes.description: CVW - This is it.  The final matches will be played this week.  Get ready by listening to the chatter of our crew - Vinnie / Jay and Robbie  The Super Six Coaches We will do some quick interviews as the coaches and teams traverse the country in an effort to get to Happy Valley Also, IN STUDIO - Finally JRo is back.  You’re welcome AmericaLee Feinswog of Destination VB - There was a huge announcement at the end of last week.  Dropped on a Friday like a Washington DC scandal to avoid the news cycle.  If you don’t know we will tell you shortly what happened.  Lee will join us to talk about the future of an iconic VB Brand.And an update on the FIVB points on the Beach Side of things.   Get out your abacus and calculator watches.

episodes.title: The Net Live 4/25/16 - Golden Weekend Edition
episodes.description:
Two former TNL Nettie Award Winners sit in on the broadcast.  That's a record!

The Men's College Super Six field is set.  Get reaction to a terrific week of college volleyball from our AVCA College Volleyball Weekly crew.  Hear predictions for the tournament and reactions to the week's events.  We will celebrate Jay's victory in proper fashion despite the fashion choices of the EIVA.

Plus, Last week you heard from Doug Beal, CEO of USAV.  This week hear from President of the USAV Board Lori Okimura on what's it's like in an Olympic year, how the BOD is approaching the search for a new CEO and what her plans are for the future.  

All that and more on TNL

episodes.title: TNL People - Powered by the AVCA:  Doug Beal - CEO of USAV
episodes.description: With the 2016 Olympics approaching Doug Beal has played one role or another in USAV for nearly 40 years.  Hear him reflect on his 12 years as CEO and his entire run with USAV.  Plus get an idea of what's next for the organization and this titan of world volleyball.  A very special TNL People.

episodes.title: TNL People - Powered by the AVCA:  April Ross - 2012 Silver Medalist
episodes.description: The Rio Summer Olympic Games are just a couple fo months away.  April Ross and partner Kerri Walsh-Jennings are pushing to qualify and medal.  April's game went to new heights last season and she hopes to build on that in 2016.  Enjoy a few minutes with arguably the best beach volleyball player in the world, April Ross.

episodes.title: TNL People - Powered by the AVCA:  Betsi Flint - 2015 AVP Rookie of the Year
episodes.description: Besti Flint won last year on the AVP Tour in Cincy.  Hear about her history and expectations for 2016 on this episode of TNL People.

episodes.title: The Net Live 4/18/16 - Start of Summer Edition
episodes.description: CVW - Vinnie / Jay and Robbie Are all about the Playoffs.  Plus Jay proves that he’s better than his Sensei.  USAV CEO Doug Beal joins us to talk about the current state of affairs headed into an olympic year, the FIVB voting and his impending retirement to a porch in ColoradoAlso, IN STUDIO - Matt Garthoff Chief Operating Officer of Vol-B-Que hangs all episode long to talk about the commercial side of VB and why VolBQue is the best thing you could do all year long.Our own Jeremy Roueche will call and talk about the Big Easy where the first tournament of the year is in the books.  Did anyone touch his stuff?  Was he fed at all?  Also, Our old friend Tim Kelly of Bring It Promotions calls in to detail a scam that has ensnared several in the VB community, INCLUDING ME!!!!!

episodes.title: The Net Live - 4/11/16   Here We Go Again
episodes.description: CVW - Vinnie / Jay and Robbie talk the end of the regular season and the start of PLAYOFFS!  Robbie is still here because Dave Kniffen made it so.Damien Scott of 2006 UCLA National Championship Team and now Ralley Point in Atlanta joins us to talk about life after volleyball and the amazing things happening in the A T L.  He is IN STUDIO. Also, IN STUDIO - Rich Lambourne rekindles his mission to take over this show and anything else I have going.  His first appearance of 2016, does this mean he breaks the curse?AVP Pro and all around stud Betsi Meter Flint will call in ahead of the start of the AVP season next week in New Orleans or Na Orlans if you prefer.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 4/4/16 - Just Another Monday Edition: Plus April Ross!!!!!!!
episodes.description:
Olympic Silver Medalist April Ross calls in ahead of the run to Rio

College VB Weekly goes off as things come down to Playoff time.

And a bunch of other stuff, including Scott Sterling!

episodes.title: The Net Live 3/28/16 - Cadbury Hangover Edition
episodes.description:
Katie Holloway and Nicole Millage of the USA Women's National Sitting Team check in after their gold medal performance in China.

CVW with the usual guys look toward the playoffs and what will become of the At Large Selections.

Plus whatever else we think of.

episodes.title: The Net Live - 3/22/16   The Who Knows Whatever Edition of TNL
episodes.description: An update from Rich Lambourne just back off two weeks in Brazil.  More college volleyball than you can stand and JRo and Barnett talk the usual talk.

episodes.title: The Net Live 03/14/16 - Lots of College Men's Volleyball Talk
episodes.description:
We're joined by Matt Werle of Grand Canyon University and Pete Hansen of THE Ohio State University fresh off a win over Long Beach.

We also discuss Kerri & April winning the FIVB Rio Grand Slam and of course, College Volleyball Weekly.

episodes.title: TNL 3/7/16 - Afternoon Delight Edition
episodes.description: Rich Lambourne is on the ground in Brazil and we have an update.  College VB is in full swing and we are on it.  Plus Kevin beat Jeremy in a musical showdown, hear the fallout from that nuclear bomb.

episodes.title: TNL People - Powered by the AVCA:  Alan Knipe of #1 LBSU Men's Head Coach
episodes.description: Alan Knipe joins Kevin and Jeremy.  Find out if the 49ers are ahead of schedule, their chaces of winning the title this year and get Alan's thoughts on his time with the National Team.

episodes.title: 2/29/16 - The Net Live Leap Year Edition
episodes.description: DJ Roueche is back from Brazil so music will be much better.  We'll be joined by Alan Knipe, Head Coach of Long Beach State Men's Team.

episodes.title: The Net Live 2/15/16
episodes.description: Get the lowdown on who has Outperformed / Underperformed or maybe just been in-line with expectations in 2016.

episodes.title: TNL People #1  - Powered by the AVCA
episodes.description: Rick McLaughin of the UC Santa Barbara Men's Volleyball team talks about his 2016 season so far and his exceptional golf game.  Episode #1 of TNL People - Powered by the AVCA

episodes.title: The Net Live brought to you by Super Photographer Ed Chan
episodes.description:
Another week of VB Coverage brought to you by the TNL Crew and sponsored by Chief Photographer for Volleyball Magazine and Director of Photography for the NVL, Ed Chan at VBshots.com

All things VB and not VB right here on TNL

episodes.description: As The Net Live begins it's 8th year, we begin with giving away our Nettie Awards, talk USA Women's National Team qualifiying for the Olympics, CVW for Men's College and other random topics that have nothing to do with volleybally

episodes.title: The Net Live 12/18/2015 LIVE from AVCA Convention in Omaha
episodes.description: Barnett and DJ Roueche will be broadcasting LIVE from the VolleyMetrics booth inside the AVCA Convention in Omaha, NE.  You never know who's going to stop by the booth and chat volleyball.  Coaches, Volleyball Brands, Players.....will all be on the couch hanging out

episodes.title: The Net Live 12/14/15 Pre-Convention Show
